e of the major writers in the American tradition, produce a fresh interpretation and understanding of this literature. Written in a straightforward style, the essays offer useful and clearly understandable criticism of some of the most important writing to come out of the United States. The theme of the collection can be stated as commitment to action based upon the individual's perception of reality: he is required to perceive reality correctly, and to commit himself to action on their basis of his perception.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Essays.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Gay Wilson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeattie, Munro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Harry Hayden, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilman, William H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffman, Frederick J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaFrance, Marston, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaFrance, Marston, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLawson, Lewis A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMillgate, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalomon, Roger B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStern, Milton R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757970840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487579708423Coveru